DEFINITION OF "EDUCATIONAL USER"

An "Educational User" means any of the following:

  (a) Accredited educational institutions, including but not limited to:
      kindergartens, primary schools, secondary schools, colleges,
      universities, community colleges, vocational schools, trade schools,
      and graduate programs.

  (b) Research institutions, including but not limited to: university
      research labs, government-funded research organizations, and
      non-profit research institutes.

  (c) Non-profit educational organizations, including but not limited to:
      libraries, museums, coding bootcamps operated as non-profits,
      educational foundations, and academic consortia.

  (d) Individual students, teachers, professors, instructors, tutors,
      teaching assistants, and researchers acting in an educational
      capacity, whether or not they are using the Software on
      institutional infrastructure. This includes personal use for
      coursework, lesson planning, academic research, thesis work,
      dissertations, and self-directed learning.

SCOPE OF "EDUCATIONAL PURPOSE"

An "Educational Purpose" means any use primarily intended for teaching,
learning, training, academic research, or curriculum development. This
includes but is not limited to:

  - Classroom instruction and demonstrations
  - Student assignments, projects, and portfolios
  - Academic research and publications
  - Thesis and dissertation work
  - Workshops, hackathons, and coding clubs at educational institutions
  - Open educational resources (OER)
  - Non-commercial conference presentations and tutorials

EXCLUSIONS FROM EDUCATIONAL USE

The following do NOT qualify as Educational Use under this license:

  - Use by for-profit companies, even for internal training programs
  - Commercial products or services, even if sold to educational institutions
  - Revenue-generating activities (e.g., paid online courses on commercial
    platforms), unless operated by a non-profit educational organization

